caption: Great night in the tap house, great service.

One of my favorites spots in down town. Rarely do I go on a weekend and not magically walk into a table. They have an excellent staff here! Excellent!! They have a huge beer selection and the bartender knew his stuff very well. I had the fish and chips which was awesome. If that wasn't enough the tartar sauce did it for me! Would not hesitate to return here!

Good place to watch the games and one of the better tap selections in Downtown Boise. Food can be hit or miss depending on how busy and who's manning the kitchen, but usually it's pretty tasty. The chicken wings are super tender and crispy, definitely worth a shot!

Went here for an NFC playoff game and we weren't sure what to expect. But we had a blast! There are more TVs per-square-inch here than anywhere I've ever been. What we loved is that they actually play the sound of the game through the speakers while the game is on, rather than play music while the game is on. Our servers were fast and friendly for how busy it was. The beer selection is good, and our food was delicious. This place is a must if you're a sports fan looking to catch the game.

The Taphouse has an outrageous assortment of beers, great food and friendly service. An extensive menu has unique and diverse selections...something for everyone.  The big drawback for me is that the place is not very large and is frequently busy so seating is difficult and service sometimes gets overwhelmed. That and the location is in heart of downtown Boise so parking is always an issue. Fortunately they are located beneath one of the parking garages so that is a plus. Still worth trying especially if your a beer afficianato and your downtown...and hungry.
